HEADWORD: philadelphus
<hw>philadelphus</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any of various chiefly
deciduous ornamental shrubs of the genus <gen>Philadelphus</gen> having
white sweet-scented flowers, single or in clusters; it is widely grown
in temperate regions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

